<subSubSection id="B0D85C1EC2093DCC6E2EB9A2FF1A3CC3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="5C5D8BBEEB9355BA262A1876B7FD61F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F027492320D541FFC7E4A15BED7CF471" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Tongbiguan Town is located in southwestern Yingjiang County, and it also belongs to the Gaoligongshan region. At the same locality, accompanying stoneflies were 
<taxonomicName id="182AC829E32CF663603BD75E8C5ABBBF" authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Neoperla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neoperla hubleyi" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hubleyi">
<emphasis id="954C48FAE73D2DA35DF146210757541B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Neoperla hubleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Stark &amp; Sivec, 2008 and one unidentified female 
<taxonomicName id="9EBB8B6723ACFBDC37A3682328798354" authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Neoperla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neoperla" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2F06F770C7C7E9226ACDF331DDCDDC9E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Neoperla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5ED1E9F8EF5E6F5D8BA2A4CCD0A1B51C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="3307FDDA6422F110426D28FEBEFA82DC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2763032DED3D3C3914AB634E170EBB02" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="1C456FB8805AE17BF74FE05EA9A08238" authorityName="Li &amp; Muranyi" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Neoperla" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neoperla lihuae" order="Plecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lihuae">
<emphasis id="245E8B3ED555C0BB0AFBD02D03566449" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Neoperla lihuae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Li &amp; 
<normalizedToken id="DD13825046B19B1B38D9D432AB2248E2" originalValue="Murányi">Muranyi</normalizedToken>
, 2014 was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation id="A207C8B1896B1A8CF371AD58E32372CB" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3753.1.1" author="Li, WH" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 9" refId="B35" refString="Li, WH, Muranyi, D, Wang, RF, 2014a. Species of Neoperla (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Yunnan Province, China. Zootaxa 3753 (1): 1 - 9, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3753.1.1" title="Species of Neoperla (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Yunnan Province, China." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3753.1.1" volume="3753" year="2014 a">Li et al. (2014a)</bibRefCitation>
from Xishuangbanna in Yunnan Province. Our specimens from Yingjiang County agree well with original description of the head pattern and terminalia, the aedeagal tube and sac.
</paragraph>
